@yxieca Thanks, The order (CABD or CBAD) is implementation defined, specifically defined by an order in python's set (more details here https://github.com/Azure/sonic-utilities/pull/1554):
```
>>> {"B", "A"}
{'A', 'B'}
```
So it will be CABD. This should be Ok, we might want to optimize the warm/fast shutdown sequence to stop A and B in parallel. Would be nice if user installed 10 independent 3rd party packages that are stopped after bgp for instance, we might save some good amount of time by parallelizing.
